How DOM Works Internally in the Browser
Step 1: Browser Receives HTML
Server sends HTML file.

Step 2: HTML → DOM Tree
Browser parser converts HTML into DOM tree.

Step 3: CSS → CSSOM Tree
CSS is parsed into CSS Object Model.

Step 4: DOM + CSSOM → Render Tree
Browser combines them.

Step 5: Layout & Paint
Browser calculates positions and displays pixels.
